in","Pupillary light reflex develops","Fingernails form"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe timing of fetal developmental milestones is important for assessing normal growth. The \u003Cstrong\u003Epupillary light reflex\u003C/strong\u003E typically develops between 32-34 weeks gestation. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options appear earlier in development:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEye-lids partially open\u003C/strong\u003E occurs around 25-26 weeks gestation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVernix caseosa\u003C/strong\u003E begins covering the skin around 20 weeks gestation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEye movements \u003C/strong\u003Ecan be seen from 14-16 weeks \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFingernails\u003C/strong\u003E form around 20 weeks gestation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThese earlier developmental milestones are typically complete by the beginning of the third trimester.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The pupillary light reflex develops late in the third trimester, typically around 31-34 weeks gestation","Eye movements can be seen from as early as 14 weeks","Physical features like vernix caseosa, fingernails, and eye opening occur during the second trimester"],"references":["Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences.","Singh, V. (2022). Textbook of clinical embryology, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Donovan T, Dunn K, Penman A, Young RJ, Reid VM. Fetal eye movements in response to a visual stimulus. Brain Behav. 2020;10(8):e01676. doi:10.1002/brb3.1676"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60754"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1597